The paper discusses the design objectives and constraints of communication engineers in the post-5G era, which is related to the field of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also introduces the concept of a semantic-effectiveness (SE) plane, which involves information filtering and control of functionalities, and is related to information theory (cs.IT), software engineering (cs.SE), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the SE plane can be seen as a core part of future communication architectures, which involves system design and control (cs.SY).
